Find Longest Continuous Growth Period



A stock analytics system in Chennai records daily stock price changes (as integers). The analyst wants to find the longest streak of consecutive increasing values (regardless of order in input).



Given an unsorted integer array nums, find:

the length of the longest consecutive sequence

Input format :
First line: integer n
Second line: n space-separated integers
Output format :
Print a single integer → length of longest consecutive sequence
Code constraints :
0 <= n <= 10^5

-10^9 <= nums[i] <= 10^9

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
6
100 4 200 1 3 2
Output 1 :
4
Input 2 :
10
0 3 7 2 5 8 4 6 0 1
Output 2 :
9
Note :
The program will be evaluated only after the “Submit Code” is clicked.
Extra spaces and new line characters in the program output will result in the failure of the test case.  




CODE:
// You are using Java-17version 
import java.util.*;
class Main{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n =  sc.nextInt();
        int[] arr = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        
        Set<Integer> set = new HashSet<>();
        for (int i : arr) {
            set.add(i);
        }
        int longestSeq = 0;
        
        for (int num : set) {
            if (!set.contains(num - 1)) {
                int currentNum = num;
                int currStreak = 1;
                while (set.contains(currentNum + 1)) {
                    currentNum += 1;
                    currStreak++;
                }
                longestSeq = Math.max(longestSeq, currStreak);
            }
        }
     
        System.out.println(longestSeq);   
    }
}

